Container:
-> core java - main method is the container -> (JVM calls the main method)
spring - IOC is the container

Container is responsible for managing the objects(beans)
    beans means object
    object <==> beans

By default the scope of beans is 'singleton'

Container is responsible for creating, managing the state and destroying the beans

In spring, the container is in the from class, we have 2 type off container
    1. Bean factory (out dated) - basic
    2. ApplicationContext (we will use this) - advanced

Note:
    -> IOC refers the beans configuration, during the object creation
    -> IOC gives the bean name, what it has configured in beans configuration.
    -> 3 types of configuration
        . xml based (outdated)
        . java based
        . annotation based

