Spring MVC:
    Model - data / business logic
    View - presentation logic
    Controller - responsible to handle the req and res (bridge btw model & view)


Spring MVC:
    @Controller -> the respose will be data + view technology
        Inorder to work with this you have to know both frontend and backend
        Thes response will be in .html/jsp/thymeleaf format

Vs

Spring restful web service:
    @RestController -> response will be only data
        You need not know frontend
        The response will be in json format / xml / plain text. It doesn't return view pages 

Languages:
    html/css/ootstrap -> frontend
    java/.net         -> backend
    sql               -> Database
    json/xml          -> message exchange from server to server (data exchange)

What is REST 
    REpresentational State Transfer
    representation -> format ex:  {
                                     id: 1
                                     name: "sachin"   
                                  }
    State -> current state

    REST was forunded by Roy Fielding, He was inspired by the concept of http, Rest is not a protocl, It is an architecture style to interact with the backend server.
    We interact using simple annotations
        Ex: @PostMapping   -> add a new resource
            @GetMapping    -> retrieve the data
            @PutMapping    -> update the data
            @DeleteMapping -> remove the data


